  {
    id: 'isa-ch-04',
    title: 'The Miracles of Isa: Signs by Allah\'s Permission',
    summary: 'Allah supported Isa with extraordinary miracles: fashioning clay into living birds, healing the blind and the leper, and raising the dead — all by Allah\'s permission. These signs were given to confirm his prophethood to the Children of Israel. Yet despite these undeniable proofs, Isa always directed attention away from himself and toward the worship of Allah alone, declaring: "Indeed, Allah is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him."',
    order: 4,
    paragraphs: [
      {
        id: 'isa-ch04-p01',
        text: 'When Isa grew to maturity and began his mission among the Children of Israel, Allah equipped him with miracles unlike any given to a prophet before or after him. The Quran details these signs: "Indeed I have come to you with a sign from your Lord in that I design for you from clay that which is like the form of a bird, then I breathe into it and it becomes a bird by permission of Allah. And I cure the blind and the leper, and I give life to the dead — by permission of Allah. And I inform you of what you eat and what you store in your houses." Each miracle was carefully chosen to address the specific challenges of his audience. The Children of Israel at that time had become proud of their physicians and healers, so Allah gave Isa the ability to cure conditions that no human doctor could treat — blindness from birth (al-akmah) and leprosy (al-abras). He was given power over life and death itself — not his own power, but always "by permission of Allah" (bi-idhnillah). This phrase is repeated five times in the Quran when describing Isa\'s miracles, emphasizing that the power belonged to Allah alone and that Isa was the instrument, not the source. Ibn Kathir explains that Isa would fashion a bird from clay, breathe into it, and the listeners would watch in astonishment as it flew away as a living creature — a direct parallel to Allah breathing life into Adam, reminding them that all life comes from the Creator alone.',
        phase: 'quran',
        references: [
          {
            type: 'quran',
            surah: 3,
            surahName: { en: 'Al-Imran', bn: 'আলে-ইমরান', ar: 'آল عمران' },
            ayahStart: 49,
            arabicText: 'وَرَسُولًا إِلَىٰ بَنِي إِسْرَائِيلَ أَنِّي قَدْ جِئْتُكُم بِآيَةٍ مِّن رَّبِّكُمْ ۖ أَنِّي أَخْلُقُ لَكُم مِّنَ الطِّينِ كَهَيْئَةِ الطَّيْرِ فَأَنفُخُ فِيهِ فَيَكُونُ طَيْرًا بِإِذْنِ اللَّهِ ۖ وَأُبْرِئُ الْأَكْمَهَ وَالْأَبْرَصَ وَأُحْيِي الْمَوْتَىٰ بِإِذْنِ اللَّهِ ۖ وَأُنَبِّئُكُم بِمَا تَأْكُلُونَ وَمَا تَدَّخِرُونَ فِي بُيُوتِكُمْ',
            translation: {
              en: 'And [make him] a messenger to the Children of Israel, [who will say], "Indeed I have come to you with a sign from your Lord in that I design for you from clay [that which is] like the form of a bird, then I breathe into it and it becomes a bird by permission of Allah. And I cure the blind and the leper, and I give life to the dead — by permission of Allah. And I inform you of what you eat and what you store in your houses."',
              bn: 'এবং তাকে বনী ইসরাঈলের কাছে রাসূল হিসেবে পাঠাবেন, [যিনি বলবেন,] "আমি তোমাদের কাছে তোমাদের রবের পক্ষ থেকে নিদর্শন নিয়ে এসেছি — আমি তোমাদের জন্য মাটি দিয়ে পাখির আকৃতি তৈরি করি, তারপর তাতে ফুঁ দিই, আর তা আল্লাহর অনুমতিতে পাখি হয়ে যায়। আমি জন্মান্ধ ও কুষ্ঠরোগীকে সুস্থ করি এবং আল্লাহর অনুমতিতে মৃতকে জীবিত করি। আর তোমরা যা খাও ও ঘরে যা সঞ্চয় করো তা আমি তোমাদের জানাই।"',
              ar: 'وَرَسُولًا إِلَىٰ بَنِي إِسْرَائِيلَ أَنِّي قَدْ جِئْتُكُم بِآيَةٍ مِّن رَّبِّكُمْ ۖ أَنِّي أَخْلُقُ لَكُم مِّنَ الطِّينِ كَهَيْئَةِ الطَّيْرِ فَأَنفُخُ فِيهِ فَيَكُونُ طَيْرًا بِإِذْنِ اللَّهِ ۖ وَأُبْرِئُ الْأَكْمَهَ وَالْأَبْرَصَ وَأُحْيِي الْمَوْتَىٰ بِإِذْنِ اللَّهِ ۖ وَأُنَبِّئُكُم بِمَا تَأْكُلُونَ وَمَا تَدَّخِرُونَ فِي بُيُوتِكُمْ'
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        id: 'isa-ch04-p02',
        text: 'Despite these extraordinary miracles, Isa\'s central message was always one of pure monotheism — the same message of every prophet from Adam to Muhammad. He declared clearly: "Indeed, Allah is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him. That is a straight path." He came not to abolish the Torah but to confirm it and to make lawful some of what had been forbidden to the Children of Israel as a mercy from Allah. On the Day of Judgment, Allah will remind Isa of all the favours bestowed upon him: "O Isa, Son of Maryam, remember My favor upon you and upon your mother when I supported you with the Pure Spirit (Ruh al-Qudus) and you spoke to the people in the cradle and in maturity; and when I taught you writing and wisdom and the Torah and the Gospel; and when you designed from clay what was like the form of a bird with My permission, then you breathed into it, and it became a bird with My permission; and you healed the blind and the leper with My permission; and when you brought forth the dead with My permission." This comprehensive recounting in Surah Al-Ma\'idah makes clear that every single miracle was "with My permission" — a point repeated six times in a single verse, leaving no room for attributing divine power to Isa himself. He was the greatest sign of Allah\'s power, but he was always and only a servant of the Almighty.',
        phase: 'quran',
        references: [
          {
