      {
        id: 'isa-ch06-p02',
        text: 'Isa\'s story does not end with his ascension. The Quran and authentic hadith confirm that he will return before the Day of Judgment. Allah says: "And indeed, he [Isa] will be [a sign for] knowledge of the Hour, so be not in doubt of it, and follow Me. This is a straight path." And regarding the People of the Book: "And there is none from the People of the Scripture but that he will surely believe in him before his death. And on the Day of Resurrection he will be against them a witness." The Prophet Muhammad (SAW) provided further details of this promised return, saying: "By Him in Whose Hand is my soul, surely the son of Maryam will soon descend amongst you as a just judge. He will break the cross, kill the swine, and abolish the jizyah. Wealth will be so abundant that no one will accept it, and a single prostration to Allah will be better than the whole world and whatever is in it." This hadith describes a time when Isa will return to earth, correct the false claims made about him, establish justice, and lead people to the worship of Allah alone. On the Day of Judgment, Allah will ask Isa: "Did you say to the people, \'Take me and my mother as deities besides Allah\'?" And Isa will reply: "Exalted are You! It was not for me to say that to which I have no right... I said not to them except what You commanded me — to worship Allah, my Lord and your Lord." This final testimony will be the definitive word on the nature of Isa: he was never anything more or less than the noble servant and messenger of Allah, a mercy to the worlds, whose miraculous life from beginning to end testifies to the limitless power of his Creator.',
        phase: 'ibn-kathir',
        references: [
